-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/ghana-s-450-million-power-plant-to-start-in-2014-b-ft-says.html
A $450 million power plant in
 Ghana , being built by a group of closely held companies, will
start operating in 2014, the Business and Financial Times
newspaper reported, citing Henry Morris, senior vice president
of  Africa Finance Corp.   The 340-megawatt Kpone Independent Power Project is funded
in part by the AFC, which is currently taking bids for the
construction of the plant, the Accra-based newspaper reported.  Cenpower Generation Co. of  Ghana  and InfraCo Ltd. are also
funding the project, according to the newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 